### 6. SketchCanvas Changes

**File: `src/modules/sketch/renderers/SketchCanvas.jsx`**

**6a. Import and render `AssemblyBoundingBoxRenderer`**

After rendering parts but before rendering dimensions, render assembly bounding boxes:

```jsx
{/* Assembly bounding boxes */}
{project.assemblies.map((asm) => {
  const asmParts = renderParts.filter(p => p.assemblyId === asm.id);
  if (asmParts.length === 0) return null;
  return (
    <AssemblyBoundingBoxRenderer
      key={asm.id}
      assembly={asm}
      parts={asmParts}
      view={activeView}
      zoom={viewport.zoom}
      isSelected={selectedId === asm.id && selectedType === 'assembly'}
      isEditMode={activeAssemblyId === asm.id}
    />
  );
})}
```

**6b. Update part selection highlight logic**

Currently, `isSelected={part.id === selectedId}` on each `PartRenderer`. In normal mode, when an assembly is selected, `selectedId` is the assembly ID, not a part ID, so individual parts will not show the selection highlight. This is correct behavior -- the assembly bounding box provides the visual feedback instead.

In edit mode, `selectedId` is a part ID, so the existing logic works correctly for individual part highlighting.

**6c. Visual dimming of non-edit-mode parts**

When in edit mode (`activeAssemblyId` is set), parts that do NOT belong to the active assembly should be visually dimmed. Pass an `opacity` or `dimmed` prop to `PartRenderer`:

```jsx
{renderParts.map((part) => (
  <PartRenderer
    key={part.id}
    part={part}
    view={activeView}
    isSelected={part.id === selectedId}
    zoom={viewport.zoom}
    dimmed={activeAssemblyId && part.assemblyId !== activeAssemblyId}
  />
))}
```

**6d. Update the keyboard handler for Escape**

The current keyboard handler in SketchCanvas dispatches `SET_TOOL` on Escape. We need to intercept Escape when in edit mode:

```js
if (e.key === 'Escape') {
  if (activeAssemblyId) {
    // Let the tool handler deal with exiting edit mode
    tool.onKeyDown(e, toolState, selectedId);
    return;
  }
  editorDispatch({ type: 'SET_TOOL', tool: 'select' });
  return;
}
```

This requires passing `activeAssemblyId` into the keyboard handler scope (it is already available via `useSketchEditor`).

**6e. Status bar edit mode indicator**

When in edit mode, the status bar should show "Editing: [assembly name]" to give clear feedback:

```jsx
{activeAssemblyId && (
  <span className={styles.statusContext}>
    Editing: {project.assemblies.find(a => a.id === activeAssemblyId)?.name || 'Assembly'}
  </span>
)}
```

